## Limitations
This report is limited by the availability of up-to-date empirical studies specifically focused on the impacts of social media on children under 13. Additionally, the perspectives gathered are primarily from Western contexts, which may not fully represent global views on the issue. Further research could explore cultural differences in attitudes towards children's use of social media.